luxR — provenance and validation notes
=========================================

This file documents, per function, whether an algorithm has been validated
against a canonical reference (prior publication, reference implementation,
etc.), or whether it is a clean-room implementation not yet validated.

light_trace() / validate_light_trace()
  Status: NOT YET IMPLEMENTED / NOT YET VALIDATED

compute_mean_light()
  Status: NOT YET IMPLEMENTED / NOT YET VALIDATED

compute_tat()
  Status: NOT YET IMPLEMENTED / NOT YET VALIDATED
  Intended reference: no canonical time-above-threshold cutoff has been
  confirmed yet; 1000 lx default is a placeholder pending literature review
  with Lucas/Mario.

compute_photic_history()
  Status: NOT YET IMPLEMENTED / NOT YET VALIDATED
  Intended reference: exponentially-weighted cumulative light exposure as
  used in circadian phase-response modelling literature (reference TBC).

compute_melanopic_edi()
  Status: NOT YET IMPLEMENTED / NOT YET VALIDATED
  Caveat: actigraphy broadband light sensors (Axivity, ActTrust) do not
  measure spectral composition, so any melanopic EDI conversion here is a
  photopic-lux approximation via a fixed calibration factor, not a true
  spectroradiometric measurement. Calibration factor and device-specific
  defaults not yet confirmed with Lucas/Mario.

compute_lri()
  Status: NOT YET IMPLEMENTED / NOT YET VALIDATED
  Intended reference: adapted from the same probability-of-same-state
  logic underlying zeitR::compute_sri() (Sleep Regularity Index), applied
  to a light/dark threshold state instead of sleep/wake.

compute_light_midpoint()
  Status: NOT YET IMPLEMENTED / NOT YET VALIDATED

find_light_onset() / find_light_offset()
  Status: NOT YET IMPLEMENTED / NOT YET VALIDATED

---
No Python reference pipeline has yet been identified for luxR (unlike
zeitR, which validates against Julia's pipeline_functions_fix27.py).
Confirm with Lucas whether a companion reference implementation exists
for any of the above before treating them as production-ready.
